 Pr( k_A=0 \text{ and }  k_B > 0) = x^{n_A } (1-x^{n_B}) 
 Pr( k_A=0 \text{ and } k_ B=1 \text{ and } k_C > 0 ) = x^{n_A + n_B} (1-x^{n_C} ) 
P(\{A\text{ contains no zeros}\}\cap \{B \text{ contains at least one zero} \}) =  
